President Obama will be honoring NCAA champion student athletes at the White House. This tradition was started by President George W. Bush. The President will welcome student athletes from various schools and sports to congratulate them on their achievements in academics, as well as in their respective sports. The event will also recognize championship teams and players for their efforts in giving back to their communities, which is part of an ongoing initiative by President Obama. Some of the schools and teams invited to attend the event include Augusta State University Men’s Golf, Boston College Men’s Ice Hockey, Duke University Men’s Lacrosse, and many others. More details, including press access information, will be released in the coming weeks.